1 A Little Survey

Here are just a few questions so I can get to know you and so you can get practice submitting an assignment in Canvas. For each question, insert your answer underneath. Make sure each answer is at the minimum a complete sentence with correctly spelled words and correct puncuation. Half the points in this assignment depend on your picture and name being correct!! Be sure to put your photo in the AAA_Owner_Info folder and call it My_photo.jpg after first renaming the current one to Koala.jpg .

1.1 Where are you now?

What row are you in, front,middle or back? Do you usually choose a similiar row in other classes? What is the computer number where you are sitting? How on a scale of 1 to 10 (1=low, 10=high) How you feel about periodic seat re-assignment, say how and why. Teams, have you ever worked on one in a class setting?

1.1.1 my answer

I am sitting in the front of the class. Yes, I am usually in the front because it keeps me from getting distracted. I dont like assigned seating because you dont get a chance to sit where you please everyday. 1 is best 10 is hate I rate it as an 8. Yes, I have worked in a class team setting.

1.2 Others and You?

What name do you prefer to be called by your classmates and instructor, if your buddys call you something but you want me to call you something else - what would that be?

1.2.1 my answer

The name I would like to be called by my instuctor and classmates is Jaynell. If I want you to call me by something else, it would be Jay.

1.3 Aspirations?

What do you want to achieve in life? What college subject do you think would be of the greatest interest to you? What degree or certificate are you trying to achieve?

1.3.1 my answer

What I want to achieve in life would be to be able to retire happy and healthy with lots of money to fall back on. the college subject that I think would be of the greatest interest to me would be Admin of Justice or anything criminal justice related. The degree I am trying to achieve would be my Bachelors in Administation of Justice. My dream profession is to be a juvenile probation officer.

1.4 Past adventures?

Have you ever gone to foreign countries, if so which ones, if not Where might you go in the future? Have you ever been in the military, if so which branch, if not which branch would you choose if you got drafted, and why?

1.4.1 my answer

I have never been to a foreign country, and because of the movie Taken, I am afraid to. If I had to travel out of country it would probably be to the Bahamas. I have never been in the military but if drafted I would want to be in the Navy because I love water.

1.5 Why are you taking Math 115?

What grade do you need to attain in stats to not upset your future plans, What is your plan?

1.5.1 my answer

The grade I must attain in stats in order to not upset my furture plans would be no lower that a C+. Of course I will try to aim for much higher than that for GPA purposes, but also just for my own satisfaction.

1.6 Homework Help and Getting around?

On a scale of 1 to 10, where 1 is a total dummy (doesnt know a mouse from a keyboard) and 10 is a complete geek (knows computer stuff in and out) How do you rate yourself? Do you have a computer you can use at home? If so, what kind is it (windows, Apple, Linux)? Do you have internet access at home?
How do you get to class? Are there issues that limit when you can be at the college?Where and when did you attend high school? Do you currently have a job?

1.6.1 my answer

On a scale of 1 to 10, 1 being a total dummy and 10 being a complete computer geek, I would rate myself an 8. I rate myself based on me being able to work or play with something on the computer or technical programs and be able to figure it out in a reasonable amount of time. Also my family calls me a genius when I simply fix the WIFI connection. Yes, I do have a windows laptop computer at home with internet access.

I drive myself to class. I have older and younger family members that is my responsiblity to take care of so that can limit me at times. I went to Palmdale High School in 2013 and graduated from there in 2017. Yes, I currectly work in the Antelope Valley Mall.
